# Changelog (F-Droid / store metadata)

This project tracks release notes in Fastlane-style metadata under:

- `fastlane/metadata/android/en-US/changelogs/<versionCode>.txt`

Rules:

- Whenever `ncarouselLocalVersionCode` is bumped in `app/build.gradle.kts`, add a matching changelog file
  named exactly `<versionCode>.txt`.
- Changelog entries should be written in **English**, short and user-facing (**2–10 lines**).
- The changelog MUST **describe the actual app changes** included in that build (not generic text).
- Prefer a clear, structured syntax (one change per line), e.g. lines starting with `- `:
  - `- Fix: …`
  - `- Add: …`
  - `- Change: …`
  - `- Security: …`
- If a release changes permissions, data handling, or scheduling behavior, mention it explicitly in the changelog.

## Release tag (required for publishing)

- **Automatic (GitHub Actions):** On every **push to `main`**, after the **Android CI** debug build succeeds, a job
  reads `ncarouselBaseVersionName` from `app/build.gradle.kts` and, if git tag `v<versionName>` is **not** already on
  `origin`, creates an annotated tag on that commit and pushes it to **GitHub**. It then **creates or updates** a
  **GitHub Release** for that tag and attaches APK assets: **`NCarousel-<version>.apk`** (release build, when CI signing
  secrets are set) and **`NCarousel-<version>-debug.apk`** (debug build).
- **New row on the Releases page** requires a **new** `ncarouselBaseVersionName` (and thus a new `v…` tag). Maintainers
  and agents bump patch+`versionCode`+changelog on every app-impacting publish (see `.cursor/rules/50-commit-push-release-automation.mdc`).
- **Forgejo mirror:** Set repository secret `FORGEJO_PUSH_TOKEN` (Forgejo personal access token with repository
  write) so the same job also pushes the tag to `https://forgejo.it/Nemeyes/NCarousel.git`. If the secret is missing,
  only GitHub gets the tag; push the tag to Forgejo manually or add the secret.
- **Manual:** You may still create `v<versionName>` locally when needed; the CI job will skip if the tag already
  exists on `origin`.
